Missions.Title: Flee the Tunnels of VORP
Missions.Description: You wake up. It's dark, and damp, and cold. There's a certain... smell... in the air. These are the Tunnels of VORP, and you must flee them.

Missions.Title: Retrieving Judy
Missions.Description: Your colleague Judy was in the advance party that went to scout VORP headquarters. Unfortunately you haven't heard anything from her since then. That's typical, because Judy plays by her own rules. Retrieve her so that she can be properly debriefed!

Missions.Title: Armory
Missions.Description: It's not clear why the VORP suddenly turned against humankind. Judy thinks that the answer dates back to the early years of the Information Age. To find the answer, you'll need to collect some outdated magnetic storage media from the VORP Armory.

Objectives.Description: Collect the outdated magnetic storage media

Missions.Title: Coming up for air
Missions.Description: "I don't understand this," you say, baffled by the data that you've recovered from the antiquated storage media. Judy suggests a nice walk in the garden might help.

Objectives.Description: Clear your head by taking a walk around

Missions.Title: Assistance needed at BASE
Missions.Description: You receive a distress call from the Benevolent Association for Symmetrical Engineering (BASE). Their development outpost on Askarian IV is being overrun by VORP agents!

Missions.Title: Back to the caves
Missions.Description: The BASE engineers have finally decrypted the files that you retrieved from VORP. It now appears that this all might have been your fault! When you escaped from the VORP crypt, you wilfully destroyed some VORP hatching pods, which take years to mature. No wonder they are pissed...

Missions.Title: Engineers' Revolt
Missions.Description: BASE are frustrated with your slow progress. They have decided to take matters into their own hands! Escape the chaos.

Missions.Title: Undercover at BASE
Missions.Description: After that last fiasco, we need to figure out what else BASE knows and isn't letting on. Investigate the BASE base and find out the basis of their base behavior!

Missions.Title: Tables Turned
Missions.Description: It turns out that the good people at BASE have been lying to us all this time. They have been secretly harvesting the coccoons of VORP to make biological weaponry. Unfortunately they are also not too happy to hear that the cat's out of the bag.

Missions.Title: Ring of Fire
Missions.Description: The illegal assets of BASE have been seized. It's your job to oversee the destruction of their weapons stockpile.....

Missions.Title: Narch of the Grenadiers
Missions.Description: BASE engineers with grenades gone MAD!

Objectives.Description: Kill them before they kill each other
